    "code": "012", 
    "data": "According to books Minhaj-un-Da’vaat and Misbah it is narrated by Hazrat Ameerul Momineen (a.s.) who said: Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) taught me this Dua and told me to recite it in the time of prosperity as well as adversity. He also told me that I should teach it to my successor and recite regularly until I go before God. He also told me that I should recite this Dua every morning and evening because this Dua is one of the treasure from the treasures of divine knowledge.\nAbi Bine Ka’ab once requested the Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) to describe the excellence of this Dua The Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) said: ‘This Dua is so excellent that even a learned man cannot describe it, but I shall narrate something about it. Whenever anyone beings to recite this Dua heavenly mercy and blessings descend upon him. God bestows upon him peace and divine mercy surrounds him. The destination of this Dua is only Divine Throne. The sound of this Dua encircles the Divine Throne with a humming sound like that of the bees and God looks upon the reciter with mercy. He who recites this Dua three times shall (Insha Allah) get his any worldly or hereafter wish fulfilled. God will free him from the punishment of the grave and remove the narrowness of his mind. He will come on the day of resurrection riding a white pearly dromedary. He will stand before God and the Lord will confer on him great honour and respect and order him to stay in paradise wherever he likes. In paradise he will be given such miraculous gifts which nobody has seen, heard or imagined.’\nHearing this Janab Salmane Farsi (r.a.) requested to describe still more. The Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) continued: ‘By God! Who has conferred on me prophethood, if this Dua is recited on a mad person, his insanity will go. If a pregnant woman feels extreme difficulty during delivery, this Dua should be recited before her and the child will be born with ease. O Salman! By Him Who sent me rightfully, if anybody recites this Dua for forty Friday nights with intention to please God, his every sin will be forgiven. If anybody recites this Dua with a clean mind his worldly sorrows and internal sicknesses shall be removed and he shall recover, O Salman! If anybody recites this Dua and goes to sleep hoping for a divine reward. God will send one thousand most respected angels whose faces are brighter than the sun and the moon for every word of this Dua, to pray for the reciter.\nJanab Salman said: ‘O Hazrat is there so much divine reward for this Dua?’ The Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) replied, ‘O Salman please don’t propagate the Divine reward of this Dua among ordinary people.’ Janab Salman (r.a.) asked: ‘O Holy one why do you command it to be concealed?’ The Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) replied: ‘O Salman! I fear that people will depend wholly upon this Dua and give up other forms of prayer. He then concluded saying that if anybody recites this Dua and dies on the very night or day he shall get the reward of a martyr. The Lord shall pardon all his sins even if he has not repented for them.’\nIt has been narrated by Sayyed Ibne Ta’oos (a.r.) in book named Mahjid Davaat from Hazrat Ameerul Momineen (a.s.) that Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) taught this Dua to him for removal of all troubles and worries. This Dua is recommended to be recited with ablution and may be recited every morning and evening. It is the one of the treasures of Arsh of Almighty God. Holy Prophet (s.a.w.a.) when requested to define the merits of this Dua. It was told by him that the merits of this Dua are many and can be seen in the above noted book.\nبِسْمِ اللَّهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِيْمِ \nBISMILLAAHIR RAHMAANIR RAHEEM\nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful.\nاَلْحَمْدُ لِلّٰهِ الَّذِیْ لاَ اِلٰہَ اِلاَّ ہُوَ الْمَلِکُ الْحَقُّ الْمُبِیْنُ \nALHAMDO LILLAAHIL LAZEE LAA ELAAHA ILLAA HOWAL MALEKUL HAQQUL MOBEENUL \nAll praise is due to Allah. There is no deity but He (who is) the Real King, the Just and Evident. \nالْمُدَبِّرُ بِلاَ وَزِیْرٍ وَّ لاَ خَلْقٍ مِّنْ عِبَادِہٖ یَسْتَشِیْرُ \nMODABBERO BELAA WAZEERINW WA LAA KHALQIM MIN E’BBADEHI YASTASHEERUL \nHe is the Administrator of (all the worlds) without any Minister; and without consults not any of his slaves. \nالْاَوَّلُ غَیْرُ مَوْصُوْفٍ وَّالْبَاقِیْ بَعْدَ فَنَآءِ الْخَلْقِ الْعَظِیْمُ \nAWWALO GHAYRO MAWSOOFIN WAL BAAQEE BA’DA FANAAA-IL KHALQIL A’ZEEMUR \nHe is the First, who cannot be described. He is Eternal and will continue to live (even) after the annihilation of all the creatures. He is the Greatest Cherisher \nالرُّبُوْبِیَّۃِ نُوْرُ السَّمٰوَتِ وَ الْاَرَضِیْنَ وَ فَاطِرُہُمَا \nROBOOBIYYATE NOORUS SAMAAWAATE WAL ARAZEENA WA FAATEROHOMAA \nand Sustainer and the Light of the earths and heavens and their Creator \nوَ مُبْتَدِعُہُمَا بِغَیْرِ عَمَدٍ خَلَقَہُمَا وَ فَتَقَہُمَا فَتْقًا \nWA MUBTADE-O’HOMAA BE GHAYRE A’MADIN KHALAQAHOMAA WA FATAQAHOMAA FATQAN \nand Marker out of nothing. He created both of them and ripped them (from each other) a proper ripping. \nفَقَامَتِ السَّمٰوٰتُ طَائِعَاتٍ بِاَمْرِہٖ وَاسْتَقَرَّتِ الْاَرْضُوْنَ \nFA QAAMATIS SAMAAWAATO TAAA-E-A’ATIN BE AMREHI WAS-TAQARRATIL ARAZOONA \nThe heavens became stable in obedience to his commandment and the earths became fixed on the surface of water \nبِاَوْتَادِہَا فَوْقَ الْمَآءِ ثُمَّ عَلاَ رَبُّنَا فِیْ السَّمٰوٰتِ الْعُلٰی \nBE AWTAADEHA FAWQAL MAAA-E SUMMA A’LAA RABBONAA FIS SAMAAWAATIL O’LAA\nwith their pegs. Then our Lord, the All-Merciful, subdued the high heavens \nاَلرَّحْمٰنُ عَلَی الْعَرْشِ اسْتَوٰی لَہٗ مَا فِی السَّمٰوَتِ وَمَا فِی الْاَرْضِ \nRAHMAANO A’LAL ARSHIS-TAWAA LAHU MAA FIS SAMAAWAATE WA MAA FIL ARZE \nand ruled from Arsh (the supreme throne in heavens). Every thing that is in heavens and in the earth \nوَ مَا بَیْنَہُمَا وَ مَا تَحْتَ الثَّرٰی فَاَنَا اَشْہَدُ بِاَنَّکَ \nWA MAA BAYNAHOMAA WA MAA TAHTAS SARAA FA-ANAA ASH-HADO BE-ANNAKA \nand in between them and what is below the earth belongs to him. So, I bear witness that verily \nاَنْتَ اللهُ لَا رَافِعَ لِمَا وَضَعَتْ وَ لاَ وَاضِعَ لِمَا رَفَعْتَ \nANTALLAAHO LAA RAA-FE-A’ LEMAA WAZA’TA WA LAA WAAZE-A’ LEMAA RAFA’TA \nThou art Allah (the only Deity). There is none to elevate what Thou hath lowered and none to lower that Thou hath elevated \nوَ لاَ مُعِزَّ لِمَنْ اَذْلَلْتَ وَ لاَ مُذِلَّ لِمَنْ اَعْزَزْتَ \nWA LAA MO-I’ZZA LEMAN AZLALTA WALAA MOZILLA LEMAN A-A’ZAZTA \nand no one to exalt him whom Thou leaveth in disgrace and no one to bring him into disgrace whom Thou exalteth \nوَ لاَ مَانِعَ لِمَنْ اَعْطَیْتَ وَ لاَ مُعْطِیَ لِمَا مَنَعْتَ \nWALAA MAANE-A’ LEMAN A-A’TAYTA WA LAA MO’TEYA LEMAA MANA’TA \nand no one to prevent him upon whom Thou bestoweth (Thou favour) and no one to bestow any thing which Thou hath withheld. \nوَ اَنْتَ اللهُ لاَ اِلٰہَ اِلاَّ اَنْتَ کُنْتَ اِذْ لَمْ تَکُنْ سَمَآءٌ مَبْنِیَّۃٌ \nWA ANTALLAAHO LAA ELAAHA ILLAA ANTA KUNTA IZ LAM TAKUN SAMAAA-UM MABNIYYATUN \nThou art Allah, there is no deity but Thou, existed when there was neither the stable sky \nوَّلاَ اَرْضٌ مَدْحِیَّۃٌ وَّلاَ شَمْسٌ مُضِیْٓئَۃٌ وَّلاَ لَیْلٌ مُظْلِمٌ \nWA LAA ARZUM MADHIYYATUN WALAA SHAMSUM MOZEE-ATUN WA LAA LAYLUM MUZLEMUN \nnor the (widely) spread up earth, nor the brilliant sun, nor the dark night, \nوَّلاَ نَہَارٌ مُضِیْئٌ وَّلاَ بَحْرٌ لُجِّیٌّ وَّلاَ جَبَلٌ رَاسٍ وَّلاَ نَجْمٌ سَارٍ \nWA LAA NAHAARUN MO-ZEEE-UN WA LAA BAHRUN LUJJIYUN WA LAA JAMALUN RAASIN WA LAA NAJMUN SAARIN \nnor the bright day, nor the vast and stormy sea, nor any sublime and stable mountain, nor any revolving planet \nوَّلاَ قَمَرٌ مُنِیْرٌ وَّلاَ رِیْحٌ تَہُبُّ وَلاَ سَحَابٌ یَسْکُبُ وَلاَ بَرْقٌ یَلْمَعُ \nWA LAA QAMARUM MONEERUN WA LAA REEHUN TAHUBBO WA LAA SAHAABUYN YASKOMO WA LAA BARQUN YALMA-O’\nnor the luminous moon nor any blowing wind nor any raining cloud, nor flashing lightning, \nوَلاَ رَعْدٌ یُسَبِّحُ وَلاَ رُوْحٌ تَنَفَّسُ وَ لاَ طَآءِرٌ یَطِیْرُ \nWA LAA RA’DUN YOSABBEHO WA LAA ROOHUN TANAFFASO WA LAA TAAA-ERUN YATEERO \nnor any praising thunder, nor any breathing soul, nor any flying bird, \nوَلاَ نَارٌ تَتَوَقَّدُ وَلاَ مَآءٌ یَطَّرِدُ کُنْتَ قَبْلَ کُلِّ شَیْءٍ وَّ کَوَّنْتَ کُلَّ شَیْءٍ \nWA LAA NAARUN TATAWAQQADO WA LAA MAAA-UN YATTAREDO KUNTA QABLA KULLE SHAYIN \nnor any blazing fire, nor any flowing water. Thou existed before the existence of every thing \nوَّ قَدَرْتَ عَلٰی کُلِّ شَیءٍ وَّ ابْتَدَعْتَ کُلَّ شَیْءٍ وَّ اَغْنَیْتَ \nWA KAWWANTA KULLA SHAYIN WABTADA’TA KULLA SHAYIN WA AGHNAYTA \nand Thou created everything and controlled everything and originated everything. Thou enriched some (people) \nوَ اَفْقَرْتَ وَ اَمَتَّ وَ اَحْیَیْتَ وَ اَضْحَکْتَ وَ اَبْکَیْتَ \nWA AFQARTA WA AMATTA WA AHYAYTA WA AZHAKTA WA ABKAYTA \nand reduced others to poverty, caused to die some (creatures) and brought others to life and made some people laugh and others weep. \nوَ عَلَی الْعَرْشِ اسْتَوَیْتَ فَتَبَارَکْتَ یَا اللهُ وَ تَعَالَیْتَ \nWA A’LAL A’RSHIS TAWAYTA FA TABAARAKTA YAA ALLAAHO WA TA-A’ALAYTA \nVerily Thou ruled from Arsh (the supreme throne in heavens). Thou art of vast blessing O Allah! Thou art Great and Supreme. \nاَنْتَ اللهُ الَّذِیْ لاَ اِلٰہَ اِلاَّ اَنْتَ الْخَلاَّقُ الْمُبِیْنُ اَمْرُکَ غَالِبٌ \nANTALLAAHUL LAZEE LAA ELAAHA ILLAA ANTAL KHALLAAQUL MO-E’ENO AMROKA GHAALEBUN \nThou art Allah and there is no deity other than Thee. Thou art the Creator and Supporter. Thy decree is overpowering \nوَ عِلْمُکَ نَافِدٌ وَ کَیْدُکَ غَرِیْبٌ وَّ وَعْدُکَ صَادِقٌ وَّ قَوْلُکَ حَقُّ \nWA I’LMOKA NAAFEZUN WA KAYDOKA GHAREEBUN WA WA’DOKA SAADEQUN WA QAWLOKA HAQQUN \nand Thy knowledge is operative. Thy strategy is wonderful; Thy promise is true; Thy word is right; \nوَّ حُکْمُکَ عَدْلٌ وَکَلٰمُکُ ہُدًی وَ وَحْیُکَ نُوْرٌ وَّ رَحْمَتُکَ وَاسِعَۃٌ \nWA HUKMOKA A’DLUN WA KALAAMOKA HODAN WA WAHYOKA NOORUN WA RAHMATOKA WAASE-A’TUN \nThy command is just; Thy utterance is right guidance and Thy Vahee (Revelation) is light. Thy mercy is vast and abundant; \nوَّ عَفْوُکَ عَظِیْمٌ وَّ فَضْلُکَ کَثِیْرٌ وَّ عَطَآؤُکَ جَزِیْلٌ وَّ حَبْلُکَ مَتِیْنٌ \nWA A’FWOKA A’ZEEMUN WA FAZLOKA KASEERUN WA A’TAAA-OKA JAZEELUN WA HABLOKA MATEENUN \nThy forgiveness is superb; Thy grace excessive; Thy gift is most respectable; Thy cord (rope) is strong; \nوَّ اِمْکَانُکَ عَتِیْدٌ وَّ جَارُکَ عَزِیْزٌ وَّ بَاْسُکَ شَدِیْدٌ وَّ مَکْرُکَ مَکِیْدٌ \nWA IMKAANOKA A’TEEDUN WA JAAROKA A’ZEEZUN WA BA-SOKA SHADEEDUN WA MAKROKA MAKEEDUN \nThy might is ever ready; Thy protégé is powerful; Thy wrath is severe and Thy stratagem is entrapping. \nاَنْتَ یَا رَبِّ مَوْضِعُ کُلِّ شَکْوٰی حَاضِرُ کُلِّ مَلاآءٍ وَّ شَاہِدُ کُلِّ نَجْوٰی \nANTA YAA RABBE MAW-ZE-O KULLE SHAKWAA HAAZERO KULLE MALAA-IN WA SHAAHEDO KULLE NAJWAA \nO Lord! With Thee are lodged all complaints. Thou art present in all gatherings and art the Witness (possessing first hand Knowledge) of all Secrets \nمُنْتَہٰی کُلِّ حَاجَۃٍ مُفَرِّجُ کُلِّ حُزْنٍ غِنٰی کُلِّ مِسْکِیْنٍ حِصْنُ کُلِّ ہَارِبٍ \nMUNTAHAA KULLE HAAJATIN MOFARREJO KULLE HUZNIN GHENAA KULLE MISKEENIN HISNO KULLE HAAREBIN \nand the ultimate goal of all supplications; the Expeller of all Sorrows; the affluence of every needy person; the stronghold for every refugee; \nاَمَانُ کُلِّ خَآءِفٍ حِرْزُ الضُّعَفَآءِ کَنْزُ الْفُقَرَآءِ مُفَرِّجُ الْغَمَّآءِ مُعِیْنُ الصَّالِحِیْنَ \nAMAANO KULLE KHAAA-EFIN HIRZUZ ZO-A’FAAA-E KANZUL FOQARAAA-E MOFARREJUL GHAMMAAA-E MO-E’ENUS SAALEHEENA \nSecurity for every terror-Stricken; a shield for the weak; a treasure for the indigent; the Destroyer of Grieves; the helper of the virtuous. \nذٰلِکَ اللهُ رَبُّنَا لاَ اِلٰہَ اِلاَّ ہُوَ تَکْفِیْ مِنْ عِبَادِکَ مَنْ تَوَکَّلَ عَلَیْکَ \nZAALEKALLAAHO RABBBONAA LAA ELAAHA ILLAA HOWA TAKFEE MIN 7E’BAADEKA MAN TAWAKKALA A’LAYKA \nSuch is Allah, our Lord. There is no deity but He Thou Satisfieth such of Thy slaves as trust unto Thee. \nوَاَنْتَ جَارُ مَنْ لاَذَبِکَ وَ تَضَرَّعَ اِلَیْکَ عِصْمَۃُ مَنِ اعْتَصَمَ بِکَ نَاصِحُ \nWA ANTA JAARO MAN LAAZABEKA WA TAZARRA-A’ ELAYKA I’’SMATO MANE’TASAMA BEKA NAASEHO \nThou art the Protector of him who is firmly attached to Thee and humiliates himself before Thee; a shield for him who seeks refuge with Thee; \nمَنِ انْتَصَرَ بِکَ تَغْفِرُ الذُّنُوْبَ لِمَنِ اسْتَغْفَرَکَ جَبَّارُ الْجَبَابِرَۃِ \nMANIN TASARA BEKA TAGHFERUZ ZONOOBA LEMANIS TAGHFARAKA JABBAARUL JABAABERATE \nthe Helper of him who looks up to Thee for help; the Forgiver of sins for him who begs Thy pardon; the Compeller of the tyrant; the Grandest of the grand; \nعَظِیْمُ الْعُظَمَآءِ کَبِیْرُ الْکُبَرَآءِ سَیِّدُ السَّادَاتِ مَوْلَی الْمَوَالِیْ \nA’ZEEMUL O’ZAMAAA-E KABEERUL KUBRAAA-E SAYYEDUS SAADAATE MAWLAL MAWAALEE \nthe Greatest of the great; the Master of masters; the Lord of lords; \nصَرِیْخُ الْمُسْتَصْرِخِیْنَ مُنَفِّسُ عَنِ الْمَکْرُوْبِیْنَ مُجِیْبُ دَعْوَۃِ الْمُضْطَرِّیْنَ\nSAREEKHUL MUSTASREKHEENA MONAFFESUN A’NIL MAKROOBEENA MOJEEBO DA’WATIL MUZTARREENA\nthe Succour of the grieved; Responder to the call of the distressed; \nاَسْمَعُ السَّامِعِیْنَ اَبْصَرُ النَّاظِرِیْنَ اَحْکَمُ الْحَاکِمِیْنَ \nASMA-U’S SAAME-E’EN ABSARUN NAAZEREEN AHKAMUL HAAKEMEEN \nthe Best of all listeners; the Best of all observers; the Best of all Judges; \nاَسْرَعُ الْحَاسِبِیْنَ اَرْحَمُ الرَّاحِمِیْنَ خَیْرُ الْغَافِرِیْنَ \nASRA-U’L HAASEBEEN ARHAMUR RAAHEMEEN KHAYRUL GHAAFEREEN \nthe Quickest of all reckoners; the Most Merciful of all the merciful; the Best of all forgivers; \nقَاضِیْ حَوَآئِجِ الْمُؤْمِنِیْنَ مُغِیْثُ الصَّالِحِیْنَ \nQAAZEYO HAWAA-EJIL MO-MENEEN MOGHEESUS SAALEHEEN \nthe Satisfier of the needs of the faithful and the Hearer of the appeals of the virtuous. \nاَنْتَ اللهُ لاَ اِلٰہَ اِلاَّ اَنْتَ رَبُّ الْعَالَمِیْنَ \nANTALLAAHO LAA ELAAHA ILLAA ANTA RABBUL A’ALAMEENA \nThou art Allah. There is no deity but Thou. Thou art the Cherisher and Sustainer of all the worlds. \nاَنْتَ الْخَالِقُ وَ اَنَا الْمَخْلُوْقُ وَ اَنْتَ الْمَالِکُ وَ اَنَا الْمَمْلُوْکُ \nANTAL KHAALEQO WA ANAL MAKHLOOQO WA ANTAL MALEKO WA ANAL MAMLOOK \nThou art the Creator and I am the creature; Thou art the Master and I am a servant; \nوَ اَنْتَ الرَّبُّ وَ اَنَا الْعَبْدُ وَ اَنْتَ الرَّازِقُ وَ اَنَا الْمَرْزُوْقُ \nWA ANTAR RABBO WA ANAL A’BDO WA ANTAR RAAAZEQO WA ANAL MARZOOK \nThou art the Lord and I am a slave; Thou art the Provider (of the means of livelihood) while I am provided with sustenance (by Thee); \nوَ اَنْتَ الْمُعْطِیْ وَ اَنَا السَّآئِلُ وَ اَنْتَ الْجَوَادُ وَ اَنَا الْبَخِیْلُ \nWA ANTAL MO’TEE WA ANAS SAAA-EL WA ANTAL JAWAADO WA ANAL BAKHEEL \nThou art the Giver while I am a beggar! Thou art Generous while I am a miser; \nوَ اَنْتَ الْقَوِیُّ وَ اَنَا الضَّعِیْفُ وَ اَنْتَ الْعَزِیْزُ وَ اَنَا الذَّلِیْلُ \nWA ANTAL QAWIYYO WA ANAZ ZA-E’EFO WA ANTAL A’ZEEZO WA ANAZ ZALEEL \nThou art the Mighty while I am weak; Thou art Noble while I am humble; \nوَ اَنْتَ الْغَنِیُّ وَ اَنَا الْفَقِیْرُ وَ اَنْتَ السَّیِّدُ وَ اَنَا الْعَبْدُ \nWA ANTAL GHANIYYO WA ANAL FAQEER WA ANTAS SAYYEDO WA ANAL A’BD \nThou art Independent while I am needy; Thou art (my) Master while I am slave; \nوَ اَنْتَ الْغَافِرُ وَ اَنَا الْمُسِیْٓئُ وَ اَنْتَ الْعَالِمُ وَ اَنَا الْجَاہِلُ \nWA ANTAL GHAAFERO WA ANAL MO-SEEE-O WA ANTAL A’ALEMO WA ANAL JAAHEL \nThou art the Forgiver of sins while I am sinful; Thou art the Omniscient while I am ignorant. \nوَ اَنْتَ الْحَلِیْمُ وَ اَنَا الْعَجُوْلُ وَ اَنْتَ الرَّحْمٰنُ وَ اَنَا الْمَرْحُوْمُ \nWA ANTAL HALEEMO WA ANAL A’ZOOL WA ANTAR RAHMAANO WA ANAL MAHROOM \nThou art Forbearing while I am hasty; Thou art All-Merciful but I have been treated with mercy! \nوَ اَنْتَ الْمُعَافِیْ وَ اَنَا الْمُبْتَلٰی وَ اَنْتَ الْمُجِیْبُ وَ اَنَا الْمُضْطَرُّ \nWA ANTAL MO-A’AFEE WA ANAL MUBTALAA WA ANTAL MOJEEBO WA ANAL MUZTARRO \nThou art the Provider of Safety but I am involved in suffering; Thou art the Responder and I am the distressed. \nوَ اَنَا اَشْہَدُ بِاَنَّکَ اَنْتَ اللهُ لاَ اِلٰہَ اِلاَّ اَنْتَ اَلْمُعْطِیْ عِبَادَکَ بِلاَ سُؤَالٍ \nWA ANAA ASH-HADO BE ANNAKA ANTALLAAHO LAA ELAAHA ILLAA ANTAL MO’TEE E’BAADAKA BELAA SO-AAALIN \nAnd I bear witness that verily Thou art Allah. There is no deity but Thou. Thou bestoweth (favours) upon Thy slaves even without their asking; \nوَ اَشْہَدُ بِاَنَّکَ اَنْتَ اللهُ الْوَاحِدُ الْاَحَدُ الْمُتَفَرِّدُ الصَّمَدُ الْفَرْدُ \nWA ASH-HADO BE ANNAKA ANTALLAAHUL AHADUL MOTAFAR-REDUS SAMADUL FARDO \nand I bear witness that verily Thou art Allah, the One, the Peerless, the Unique, the Independent and the Single \nوَ اِلَیْکَ الْمَصِیْرُ وَ صَلَّی اللهُ عَلٰی مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ اَہْلِ بَیْتِہِ الطَّیِّبِیْنَ الطَّاہِرِیْنَ \nWA ELAYKAL MASEERO WA SALLALLAAHO A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AHLE BAYTEHIT TAYYEBEENAT TAAHEREENA \nand verily to Thee we must return. Blessings of Allah be upon Mohammad (s.a.w.a.) and his AhleBait (kinsfolk), the holy and pure. \nوَ اغْفِرْلِیْ ذُنُوْبِیْ وَاسْتُرْ عَلَیَّ عُیُوْبِیْ وَ افْتَحْ لِیْ مِنْ لَّدُنْکَ رَحْمَۃً \nWAGH-FIRLEE ZONOOBEE WASTUR A’LAYYA O’YOOBEE WAFTAH LEE MIN LADUNKA RAHMATAN \nAnd O Lord; forgive my sins and keep my faults concealed and extend to me Thy special mercy \nوَّ رِزْقًا وَّاسِعًا یَا اَرْحَمَ الرَّاحِمِیْنَ وَالْحَمْدُ لِلّٰہِ رَبِّ الْعٰلَمِیْنَ \nWA RIZQAN WAASE-A’N YAA ARHAMAR RAAHEMEENA WAL HAMDO LILLAAHE RABBIL A’ALAMEENA \nand bounties of sustenance. O the All-Merciful! All the praise is due to Allah the Cherisher and Sustainer of all the worlds. \nوَحَسْبُنَا اللهُ وَ نِعْمَ الْوَکِیْلُ وَلاَ حَوْلَ وَ لاَ قُوَّۃَ اِلاَّ بِاللهِ الْعَلِیِّ الْعَظَیْمِ.\nWA HASBONALLAAHO WA NE’MAL WAKEEL WA LAA HAWLA WALAA QUWWATA ILLAA BILLAHIL A’LIYYIL A’ZEEM.\nAnd for us Allah is sufficient (helper) and the excellent Protector. There is neither might nor power but with Allah, the Great and High. ", 
    "title": "Dua Yastasheer"
}